# Content Conventions (i18n JSON)

## File Structure

All content lives in `messages/it.json` and `messages/en.json`. Both files must have identical key trees.

## Namespace Convention

```json
{
  "Metadata": {},
  "Hero": {},
  "Manifesto": {},
  "Services": {
    "operating-partner": {},
    "formazione": {}
  },
  "CaseStudy": {
    "progetto-alfa": {}
  },
  "Common": {
    "cta": {},
    "footer": {},
    "nav": {}
  },
  "Offerta": {}
}
```

- Homepage sections use top-level namespaces: `Hero`, `Manifesto`, `Partners`, `Services`, `FAQ`, etc.
- New service pages: `Services.<slug>`.
- New case study pages: `CaseStudy.<slug>`.
- Shared strings (CTAs, footer, nav): `Common.<group>`.

## Key Naming

- camelCase for keys: `sectionTitle`, `ctaPrimary`, `heroHeadline`.
- Nested objects for logical groups: `proof.blocks.1.number`.
- Numbered items use string indices: `items.1.q`, `items.2.q`.

## Copy Rules

- Never hardcode copy in TSX. Always use `t("key")` or `useTranslations()`.
- Meta description: 150-160 characters.
- One H1 per page (mapped to the main headline key).
- IT is the primary language; EN is a professional translation.
- Keep IT and EN files in sync: same keys, same structure.
